The paper focuses on evaluating and comparing generative models for Continual Learning on image generation tasks, which suggests that it could fall under several sub-categories. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper involves training and evaluating machine learning models, specifically generative models, on sequential tasks. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper focuses on image generation tasks, which is a subfield of computer vision. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper involves training and evaluating AI models, specifically generative models, on sequential tasks. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper involves training and evaluating neural networks, which falls under the subfield of neural computing. 

cs.CL (Computation and Language): While not the primary focus, the paper does involve natural language processing in terms of describing the models and tasks.
